==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monogenic
<hw>Mon`o*gen"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to monogenesis.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Producing only one kind of germs,
or young; developing only in one way.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monogenism</ent>⟦br⟧
